create "local" user.  The wrapper scripts should be run from
the regular user account.  The scripts use sudo to invoke the
individual tests as "local" user.  

If you want to have a different name for the TESTUSER than local,
change gen_audit_spade.sh and set the value of "TESTUSER"


set SPADE_HOME in gen_audit_spade.sh

build the binaries
cd tests
./build.csh

create master files:
./gen_master_cdm.csh tests

run unit tests
./run_gen_audit.csh tests

run unit tests randomly
./run_rand_audit.csh tests

  

